# Conekta Elements - Web Application Rules

## Project Context

This is the **Web Application** part of Conekta Elements, a monorepo with:
- `webApp/` - React + TypeScript (this project)
- `shared/` - Kotlin Multiplatform SDK with Compose UI

**Current Phase:** Express Checkout only (Apple Pay / Google Pay)

## Architecture: Feature-Based

Everything related to a feature lives together in one folder.

```
src/
├── features/
│   └── express-checkout/        # Phase 1
│       ├── components/
│       ├── hooks/
│       ├── store/
│       ├── utils/
│       └── index.ts            # Public API
├── lib/                        # Formatters, constants
├── api/                        # HTTP client, endpoints
├── providers/                  # ConektaProvider
└── styles/                     # Mantine theme
```

## Core Principles

### 1. Feature Encapsulation
- Everything for Express Checkout stays in `/features/express-checkout/`
- Export only public API via `index.ts`
- Internal components/hooks/utils stay private

### 2. TypeScript Strict Mode
- Always define explicit types
- No `any` - use `unknown` if needed
- Use interfaces for public APIs
- Use types for internal implementations

### 3. Mantine Components
- Use Mantine as base for all UI components
- Customize via theme in `/styles/theme.ts`
- Use `sx` prop for component-specific styles
- Avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary

### 4. Zustand for State (if needed)
- Create store in `features/express-checkout/store/`
- Use selectors to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Keep store focused and minimal

### 5. Custom Hooks
- Extract logic from components into hooks
- Place in `features/express-checkout/hooks/`
- Name with `use` prefix

## File Structure

### Express Checkout Feature

```
features/express-checkout/
├── components/
│   ├── ExpressCheckout.tsx          # Main component (public)
│   ├── ApplePayButton.tsx           # Internal
│   └── GooglePayButton.tsx          # Internal
├── hooks/
│   └── usePaymentMethod.ts          # Auto-detection logic
├── store/
│   └── expressCheckoutStore.ts      # Zustand (if needed)
├── utils/
│   └── detectPaymentMethod.ts       # Device/browser detection
└── index.ts                         # Public exports only

// index.ts exports:
export { ExpressCheckout } from './components/ExpressCheckout';
export type { ExpressCheckoutProps } from './components/ExpressCheckout';
```

## TypeScript Guidelines

### Interfaces & Types

```typescript
// Public API - use interface
interface ExpressCheckoutProps {
  publicKey: string;
  amount: number;
  currency: string;
  onPaymentCompleted: (result: PaymentResult) => void;
}

// Discriminated unions for state
type PaymentMethodType = 'apple_pay' | 'google_pay' | null;

type PaymentResult = 
  | { status: 'success'; data: PaymentData }
  | { status: 'error'; error: string };
```

### No Any

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
const handlePayment = (data: any) => { ... }

// ✅ Good
const handlePayment = (data: PaymentData) => { ... }
```

## React Patterns

### Component Structure

```typescript
import { Button } from '@mantine/core';

interface ApplePayButtonProps {
  amount: number;
  onClick: () => void;
}

export const ApplePayButton = ({ amount, onClick }: ApplePayButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <Button
      variant="filled"
      size="lg"
      onClick={onClick}
    >
      Pay ${(amount / 100).toFixed(2)} with Apple Pay
    </Button>
  );
};
```

### Custom Hooks

```typescript
// features/express-checkout/hooks/usePaymentMethod.ts
export const usePaymentMethod = () => {
  const [method, setMethod] = useState<PaymentMethodType>(null);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    const detected = detectPaymentMethod();
    setMethod(detected);
  }, []);
  
  return method;
};
```

### Zustand Store (if needed)

```typescript
// features/express-checkout/store/expressCheckoutStore.ts
import { create } from 'zustand';

interface ExpressCheckoutStore {
  isProcessing: boolean;
  setIsProcessing: (value: boolean) => void;
}

export const useExpressCheckoutStore = create<ExpressCheckoutStore>((set) => ({
  isProcessing: false,
  setIsProcessing: (value) => set({ isProcessing: value }),
}));

// Usage with selector (for performance)
const isProcessing = useExpressCheckoutStore(state => state.isProcessing);
```

## Mantine Usage

### Theme Configuration

```typescript
// styles/theme.ts
import { createTheme } from '@mantine/core';

export const conektaTheme = createTheme({
  primaryColor: 'blue',
  fontFamily: 'Inter, sans-serif',
  radius: { md: '8px' },
  spacing: { md: '16px' },
});
```

### Component Styling

```typescript
// Use Mantine props
<Button variant="filled" size="lg" radius="md">
  Click me
</Button>

// Use sx for custom styles
<Button 
  sx={(theme) => ({
    backgroundColor: theme.colors.blue[6],
    '&:hover': {
      backgroundColor: theme.colors.blue[7],
    },
  })}
>
  Custom
</Button>
```

## File Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `ExpressCheckout.tsx`)
- Hooks: `useCamelCase.ts` (e.g., `usePaymentMethod.ts`)
- Utils: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `detectPaymentMethod.ts`)
- Stores: `camelCaseStore.ts` (e.g., `expressCheckoutStore.ts`)
- Types: `types.ts` or colocated in component file

## Express Checkout Specific

### Auto-Detection Logic

```typescript
// utils/detectPaymentMethod.ts
export const detectPaymentMethod = (): PaymentMethodType => {
  // Check Apple Pay
  if (window.ApplePaySession?.canMakePayments()) {
    return 'apple_pay';
  }
  
  // Check Google Pay
  if (window.google?.payments?.api) {
    return 'google_pay';
  }
  
  return null;
};
```

### Compliance by Design
- Follow Apple Pay Human Interface Guidelines
- Follow Google Pay Brand Guidelines
- Enforce minimum button sizes (height: 40px+)
- Use official button styles only
- Support dark/light themes

## Testing

### Component Tests

```typescript
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { ExpressCheckout } from './ExpressCheckout';

describe('ExpressCheckout', () => {
  it('shows Apple Pay on iOS', () => {
    window.ApplePaySession = { canMakePayments: () => true } as any;
    
    render(<ExpressCheckout amount={10000} currency="MXN" />);
    
    expect(screen.getByText(/apple pay/i)).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

### Hook Tests

```typescript
import { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react';
import { usePaymentMethod } from './usePaymentMethod';

describe('usePaymentMethod', () => {
  it('detects Apple Pay', () => {
    window.ApplePaySession = { canMakePayments: () => true } as any;
    
    const { result } = renderHook(() => usePaymentMethod());
    
    expect(result.current).toBe('apple_pay');
  });
});
```

## Code Quality

### ESLint & Prettier
- Use provided configs
- Run `npm run lint` before commit
- Run `npm run format` to auto-fix

### Performance
- Use React.memo for pure components
- Use Zustand selectors to prevent re-renders
- Lazy load components if needed

### Accessibility
- All buttons must be keyboard accessible
- Provide ARIA labels where needed
- Test with screen readers
- Support high contrast mode

## Anti-Patterns

❌ **Don't**
- Mix business logic in UI components
- Use inline styles (use Mantine or sx)
- Import from other feature internals
- Mutate state directly
- Use `any` type
- Ignore TypeScript errors
- Skip tests

✅ **Do**
- Use Mantine components
- Extract logic to hooks
- Keep components small
- Use explicit types
- Write tests
- Follow file naming conventions

## Code Review Checklist

- [ ] Code in correct feature folder
- [ ] Public API exported via index.ts
- [ ] TypeScript types explicit
- [ ] Uses Mantine components
- [ ] No business logic in UI components
- [ ] Accessible (keyboard + ARIA)
- [ ] Tests included
- [ ] No console.logs

